  "texts": [
    "The only practical effect of a central singular density is to make the central image unobservable (cf.",
    "Sect. 3.4 above).",
    "Thus, if no central image is observable, modelling the configuration with a central singularity is convenient.",
    "Another singular property of the isothermal sphere is that the total mass is formally infinite.",
    "This follows from the density expression (58) and is the reason for M not appearing in the expressions for this model."
